    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-07T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="802"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.34/12–747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-07T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 7, 1947—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 7—9:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2346. Chinese concur in modifications press release (Deptel 1479, December 5) re
                    signing agreement transfer naval vessels. Texts of agreement and exchange of
                    notes will not be released.</p>
                <p>We anticipate that omission of texts will cause widespread speculation as to
                    nature of agreement and possible secret terms particularly inasmuch as press
                    releases in connection with signing Fulbright and post-UNRRA agreements included
                        texts.<note n="78" xml:id="d802fn1">For correspondence on these subjects,
                        see <ref target="#pg_1263">pp. 1263</ref> ff. and <ref target="#pg_1293">pp.
                            1293</ref> ff., respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <p>We assume that agreement will be registered with UN<note n="78a" xml:id="d802fn2"
                        >United Nations.</note> and would judge from last sentence Deptel 1387,
                    November 14 that action by Bofors unlikely. In view foregoing we of opinion that
                    speculation which will inevitably result from failure to release text may do
                    more harm than would publication of clause re Bofors claim and urge Department
                    explore matter further with Navy with view to releasing text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
